OL,3,CPeople urged to 'use water wisely' as
OL,4,Criver levels drop across Wales
OL,6,FWales is one step closer to an
OL,7,Fofficial drought after prolonged
OL,8,Fperiods of dry weather this May.
OL,10,FNatural Resources Wales (NRW) has
OL,11,Furged people and businesses to use
OL,12,Fwater wisely and confirmed Wales'
OL,13,FDrought Liason Group will meet this
OL,14,FThursday (22nd May) to understand if
OL,15,Fstronger advice is needed.
OL,17,FWelsh Water also advised it's
OL,18,Fcustomers to think about their water
OL,19,Fusage last Saturday (17th May). They
OL,20,Fsaid reservoir levels are lower than
OL,21,Fexpected for this time of year.
